

<script>
	function status(msg) {
		var a = document.getElementById("status")
		a.innerHTML = msg;
	}
</script>
<div class="box yellow">
<div id="form">
<!--
	I should make it a timer, and have a status
-->
<% remote_form_for(:example,
                   :url => { :action => 'add' }, :update => 'status',
				   :loading => 'status("Saving and Analyzing...<blink.</blink>")'
                   
					) do |form| %>
				<b>Enter the URL to your phpinfo() page.</b><br/>
					<i>i.e. https://secure18.easycgi.com/phpinfo.php</i>
				<%= text_field_tag "url", "http://", :id => "url_box" %>
				<%= submit_tag "Load", :id => "submit" %>
	
<% end -%>
</div>
<div id="status"></div>

</div>

<div class="box">
<p>The PHP DNA project is an attempt to collect and analyze the output from a large number of phpinfo() pages from around the world.
We have currently indexed <b><%=@stats_total%></b> phpinfo() pages, and have a library of <b><%=@stats_mods%></b> modules and 
<b><%=@stats_attributes_key%></b> attribute keys with <b><%=@stats_attributes_val%></b> unique values.
</p>


<p>The PHP DNA project is made possible by the generous support of the <a href="http://si.umich.edu" target="_blank">University of Michigan School of Information</a>

</p>
</div>


<div class="box">
<h3>Recent Additions</h3>
<ul>
<% @recent.each do |r| %>
	<%
	#p r.site
	#p r.id
	%>
	<li><a href="/phpinfo/<%=r.id%>"><%=r.site.host%></a></li>
<% end %>
</ul>

</div>
